targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) AS "time",
  entity_id,
  uncertain,
  user_id,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor)
  AND user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  time,
  entity_id,
  uncertain,
  user_id,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2
ORDER BY
  time ASC

SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) as time,
  COUNT(*) AS "metric"
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  user_id IN ($user_id)
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor)
GROUP BY
  time
ORDER BY
  time;

SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) as time,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2,
  COUNT(*) as "count"
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2,
  time
ORDER BY
  time

panels.description: Se usan colores o tamaños de puntos para representar el nivel de incertidumbre en las mediciones donde los puntos con una incertidumbre baja son más grandes y de un color más intenso que los puntos con una incertidumbre alta.

GROUP BY
  time,
  x1,
  y1,
  uncertain,
  user_id
ORDER BY
  time ASC

Es una curva suave con forma de campana donde el pico representa el valor más común y el ancho de la "campana" muestra cuánta variación hay en los datos. Esto es útil para mostrar cuánto varía una métrica con respecto al promedio.

  x1 as x1,

  y1 as y1,
  y2 as y2,

FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor) AND user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  time,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2,
  uncertain
ORDER BY
  time

  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) AS "time", 
  user_id,
  COUNT(*) AS activity
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor) AND user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  time,
  user_id
ORDER BY
  time;
